## Code of Conduct

This project adheres to the Contributor Covenant, version 2.1, available at [Contributor Covenant](https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/2/1/code_of_conduct/).

In summary, we strive to create a welcoming and inclusive community for all. We expect everyone who interacts with the project to follow these principles:

**Be respectful:** Treat all participants with respect. Avoid personal attacks, harassment, discrimination, and other forms of unprofessional conduct.

**Be considerate:** Be mindful of your language and actions. We value diversity and encourage open and respectful discussion.

**Be collaborative:** Work collaboratively to achieve the project's goals. Be open to constructive criticism and feedback.

**Be responsible:** Take responsibility for your own actions and words. Avoid making offensive or harmful statements.

**Resolve conflicts constructively:** If you encounter a conflict, work with others to resolve it constructively and respectfully.

**Additional information:**

- If you have any questions or concerns, please contact the project maintainers.
- If you experience or witness behavior that violates this Code of Conduct, please report it to the project maintainers.
- Reports will be handled confidentially and investigated fairly.
- Project maintainers reserve the right to take appropriate action, including warning, removal of comments or contributions, or temporary or permanent bans, for violations of this Code of Conduct.